You can do this with two elements with the same content stacked on top of each other using `clip-path`. Note: clip path isn&#39;t widely supported yet.

https://caniuse.com/#search=clip-path

This is a very basic example and you will most likely need to adjust things for your needs.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .wrapper {
      position: relative;
    }

    .box {
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 30px;
      position: absolute;
      padding: 100px;
    }

    .red-bg {
      background: red;
      color: yellow;
      z-index: 3;
      clip-path: polygon(100% 0, 0 0, 0 100%);
    }

    .yellow-bg {
      background: yellow;
      color: red;
      z-index: 2;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;div class=&quot;wrapper&quot;&gt;
